snippet: The two sides said they had reached agreement on sharing power in Muslim-dominated parts of the south and hoped to reach a final peace agreement by January.
abstract: Philippines has moved a step closer to landmark deal with the Moro Islamic Liberation Front, country's largest Muslim insurgent group, but significant obstacles to an end to violence remain.
lead_paragraph: The two sides said they had reached agreement on sharing power in Muslim-dominated parts of the south and hoped to reach a final peace agreement by January.

headline.main: Philippines and Muslim Rebels Move Closer to Final Peace Deal
headline.print_headline: The Philippines: Peace Accord With Rebels Moves Forward
